<div class=3D"mw-heading mw-heading2"><h2 id=3D"Converting_numbers">Convert=
ing numbers</h2><span class=3D"mw-editsection"><span class=3D"mw-editsectio=
n-bracket">[</span><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/w/index.php?title=3D=
Scientific_notation&amp;action=3Dedit&amp;section=3D10" title=3D"Edit secti=
on: Converting numbers"><span>edit</span></a><span class=3D"mw-editsection-=
bracket">]</span></span></div>
<p>Converting a number in these cases means to either convert the number in=
to scientific notation form, convert it back into decimal form or to change=
 the exponent part of the equation. None of these alter the actual number, =
only how it's expressed.
</p>
<div class=3D"mw-heading mw-heading3"><h3 id=3D"Decimal_to_scientific">Deci=
mal to scientific</h3><span class=3D"mw-editsection"><span class=3D"mw-edit=
section-bracket">[</span><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/w/index.php?ti=
tle=3DScientific_notation&amp;action=3Dedit&amp;section=3D11" title=3D"Edit=
 section: Decimal to scientific"><span>edit</span></a><span class=3D"mw-edi=
tsection-bracket">]</span></span></div>
<p>First, move the decimal separator point sufficient places, <i>n</i>, to =
put the number's value within a desired range, between 1 and 10 for normali=
zed notation. If the decimal was moved to the left, append <code class=3D"n=
owrap">=C3=97 10<i><sup>n</sup></i></code>; to the right, <code class=3D"no=
wrap">=C3=97 10<i><sup>=E2=88=92n</sup></i></code>. To represent the number=
 <span class=3D"nowrap"><span data-sort-value=3D"7006123040000000000=E2=99=
=A0"></span>1,230,400</span> in normalized scientific notation, the decimal=
 separator would be moved 6 digits to the left and <code class=3D"nowrap">=
=C3=97 10<sup>6</sup></code> appended, resulting in <span class=3D"nowrap">=
<span data-sort-value=3D"7006123040000000000=E2=99=A0"></span>1.2304<span s=
tyle=3D"margin-left:0.25em;margin-right:0.15em;">=C3=97</span>10<sup>6</sup=
></span>. The number <span class=3D"nowrap"><span data-sort-value=3D"300259=
6790000000000=E2=99=A0"></span>=E2=88=920.004<span style=3D"margin-left:.25=
em;">0321</span></span> would have its decimal separator shifted 3 digits t=
o the right instead of the left and yield <span class=3D"nowrap"><span data=
-sort-value=3D"3002596790000000000=E2=99=A0"></span>=E2=88=924.0321<span st=
yle=3D"margin-left:0.25em;margin-right:0.15em;">=C3=97</span>10<sup>=E2=88=
=923</sup></span> as a result.
</p>
<div class=3D"mw-heading mw-heading3"><h3 id=3D"Scientific_to_decimal">Scie=
ntific to decimal</h3><span class=3D"mw-editsection"><span class=3D"mw-edit=
section-bracket">[</span><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/w/index.php?ti=
tle=3DScientific_notation&amp;action=3Dedit&amp;section=3D12" title=3D"Edit=
 section: Scientific to decimal"><span>edit</span></a><span class=3D"mw-edi=
tsection-bracket">]</span></span></div>
<p>Converting a number from scientific notation to decimal notation, first =
remove the <code class=3D"nowrap">=C3=97 10<i><sup>n</sup></i></code> on th=
e end, then shift the decimal separator <i>n</i> digits to the right (posit=
ive <i>n</i>) or left (negative <i>n</i>). The number <span class=3D"nowrap=
"><span data-sort-value=3D"7006123040000000000=E2=99=A0"></span>1.2304<span=
 style=3D"margin-left:0.25em;margin-right:0.15em;">=C3=97</span>10<sup>6</s=
up></span> would have its decimal separator shifted 6 digits to the right a=
nd become <span class=3D"nowrap"><span data-sort-value=3D"70061230400000000=
00=E2=99=A0"></span>1,230,400</span>, while <span class=3D"nowrap"><span da=
ta-sort-value=3D"3002596790000000000=E2=99=A0"></span>=E2=88=924.0321<span =
style=3D"margin-left:0.25em;margin-right:0.15em;">=C3=97</span>10<sup>=E2=
=88=923</sup></span> would have its decimal separator moved 3 digits to the=
 left and be <span class=3D"nowrap"><span data-sort-value=3D"30025967900000=
00000=E2=99=A0"></span>=E2=88=920.004<span style=3D"margin-left:.25em;">032=
1</span></span>.
</p>
<div class=3D"mw-heading mw-heading3"><h3 id=3D"Exponential">Exponential</h=
3><span class=3D"mw-editsection"><span class=3D"mw-editsection-bracket">[</=
span><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/w/index.php?title=3DScientific_not=
ation&amp;action=3Dedit&amp;section=3D13" title=3D"Edit section: Exponentia=
l"><span>edit</span></a><span class=3D"mw-editsection-bracket">]</span></sp=
an></div>
<p>Conversion between different scientific notation representations of the =
same number with different exponential values is achieved by performing opp=
osite operations of multiplication or division by a power of ten on the sig=
nificand and an subtraction or addition of one on the exponent part. The de=
cimal separator in the significand is shifted <i>x</i> places to the left (=
or right) and <i>x</i> is added to (or subtracted from) the exponent, as sh=
own below.
</p>
